result.execSummary:
The defendant Justice J Fox was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operate w/o Valid License(2nd w/in3 Yrs), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.05(3)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

2:31 p.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Joey Roeth.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Court recites agreement - defendant will plea to count 1 in 2016CF39, count 1 in 2016CF57 and counts 3 & 4 in 2016cf147.  State concurs.  Atty Roeth concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  (If felony) Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on count 1 in 2016CF39 and orders counts 2 & 3 be dismissed and read-in, finds the defendant guilty on count 1 in 2016CF57 and orders count 2 be dismissed and read-in and finds the defendant guilty on counts 3 & 4 in 2016CF147 and orders counts 1,2 & 5 be dismissed and read-in.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  DA confirms compliance with victim witness rights.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Roeth.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

2016CF39 (count 1)

-SWD, and places the defendant on probation for 3 years.

CONDITIONS:

-Court costs.  To be paid to the Clerk of Courts office.  Monies are to be paid during the term of probation.
-Random drug testing.
-AODA and any follow-up
-DNA sample.

2016CF57 (Count 1)

-5 days county jail to commence within 60 days.  Court grants huber, out of county service and out of county travel.
-Court costs.  To be paid during the term of probation.
-DNA sample.

2016CF147 (count 3)

-Count 3 - 10 days county jail consecutive to 16CF57.  Court grants huber, out of county service and out of county travel.
-Court costs.  To be paid during the term of probation.
-DNA Sample

2016CF147 (Count 4)

-SWD and places the defendant on probation for 24 months.

CONDITIONS:

-Court costs. To be paid to the Clerk of Courts office.  Monies are to be paid during the term of probation.
-Defendant is to abide by all rules and recommendations of the supervising agent including any counseling and/or treatment as recommended.
-DNA sample.
